    &lt;Title&gt;Ward 8 Solihull&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My Nan is currently staying on ward 8, she has been at Solihull now for a week so far after a 2 week stay at another hospital. The difference in care is like night and day. I understand how busy these wards can be but at Solihull nothing seems to much for any of the nurses healthcare assistants just any of the staff they are always happy friendly approachable and restore my faith in the nhs after a horrific few weeks at the other hospital. I would just like to let the hospital and the staff know that the little things they do may feel like they are unnoticed that extra moment to ask if an elderly patient who has no visitors needs anything. The hair stroke while they have blood taken it’s all noticed. I have watch the staff interact with my nan and the other patients in her bay and they adapt to each individual in a way that amazes me to make sure they are getting the care they need. Not enough praise is given to the people who work hard as people are always quick to complain. The improvement in my nans condition has come on leaps and bounds since moving to Solihull and I completely 100% believe that is down to the staff and the level of care she is receiving during her recovery at this rate she’ll be home before we know it! Thank you to all staff on ward 8 I really hope this gets back to you all as I really want everyone to know that your hard work and excellent  work does not go unproved!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
